results.name: Smallest number m such that A186711(m) = A003586(n).
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: n = 10: A003586(10) = 18 and A186711(23) = 18 with no preceding occurrences of 18 in A186711.
maple: A186712 := proc(n) for m from 1 do if A186711(m) = A003586(n) then return m; end if; end do: end proc: # _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 04 2011
program: a186712 n = (+ 1) $ fromJust $ findIndex (== a003586 n) a186711_list
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Feb 26 2011
